Diagnosis. Differs from other consubgeners by the wide, rounded posterior opisthomere process ( pp ) considerably exceeding the solenomere (
Figs 12 a–b, 12 d
), and by the bottle-like (i.e. basally wide, then narrowing) posterior solenomere process ( psp ) being only slightly shorter than the anterior one ( asp ) (
Figs 12 b, 12 d
).

The male from Szentmargitfalva (
Hungary
) had setiform filaments on the opisthomere’s flagellum-conducting lamella.
